1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,640
Hello English learners, welcome back to EnglishPod.
英语学习者你们好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:05,640
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,640
And I'm Erica.
我是Erica。

4
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:10,720
And today we're bringing you the next part of our suspense series, The New Guy in Town.
今天我们带来悬疑系列的下一个部分，《镇上的新面孔》。

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,720
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:15,440
So we know that Armando wasn't really a vampire, that he was just acting.
所以我们知道Armando其实不是吸血鬼，他只是在演戏。

7
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:19,400
And the women aren't quite what they seem in this dialogue.
而在这段对话里，那些女人也不是表面看起来的样子。

8
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:24,240
In the last one, something happened and she transformed into some sort of, I don't know,
在上一集里，发生了点事，她变成了某种，我也不知道，

9
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,240
creature, right?
生物，对吧？

10
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:26,240
Like monster.
像怪物一样。

11
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:27,240
Right.
对。

12
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:28,580
So now let's see what happens.
现在我们来看看发生了什么。

13
00:00:28,580 --> 00:00:31,400
So we're not going to preview any vocabulary this time.
这次我们不预览任何词汇。

14
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:35,040
Let's just listen to the dialogue and see what happens.
直接听对话，看看会发生什么。

15
00:00:35,040 --> 00:00:47,520
What the heck is going on?
这到底是怎么回事？

16
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,520
Did you see that?
你看到了吗？

17
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:49,520
What was that thing?
那是什么东西？

18
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,520
I don't know.
我不知道。

19
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,520
I'm just glad we made it out.
我很高兴我们逃出来了。

20
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:52,520
Look, there's a police car.
看，有辆警车。

21
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:53,520
Help!
救命！

22
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:54,520
Help!
救命！

23
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,520
Please, please stop!
请，请停车！

24
00:00:55,520 --> 00:01:06,520
Howdy, ma'am.
你好，女士。

25
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:08,960
What seems to be the problem?
出什么问题了？

26
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:10,880
Is this man bothering you?
这个男人在骚扰你吗？

27
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:12,160
Officer, officer.
警官，警官。

28
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:14,740
There is like a witch creature back there.
后面有个像女巫一样的怪物。

29
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:19,000
We tied her up, but she broke free and she was about to have us for dinner.
我们把她绑起来了，但她挣脱了，还差点把我们当晚餐。

30
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,560
Okay, calm down.
好了，冷静点。

31
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,840
Calm down.
冷静点。

32
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:24,240
Let me see your eyes, please.
请让我看看你的眼睛。

33
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:26,720
Have you been drinking tonight, son?
今晚喝酒了吗，小伙子？

34
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,920
We're telling the truth.
我们说的是实话。

35
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:29,920
She's in there.
她就在里面。

36
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:37,360
We suspected her being a kidnapper or a rapist, but it turns out she's an alien or something.
我们怀疑她是绑架犯或强奸犯，但结果她是个外星人什么的。

37
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:39,160
Okay, calm down.
好了，冷静点。

38
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:40,160
Calm down.
冷静点。

39
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,640
Let me see your eyes, please.
请让我看看你的眼睛。

40
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,640
Seriously.
说真的。

41
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:46,320
Are you going to help us out or not?
你到底帮不帮我们？

42
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:47,320
Okay.
好吧。

43
00:01:47,320 --> 00:02:02,320
Let's go have a look, shall we?
我们去看看，好吗？

44
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:15,920
Hello?
喂？

45
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:19,080
Is anyone in there?
里面有人吗？

46
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,080
Be careful.
小心点。

47
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:31,200
She might be hiding.
她可能躲起来了。

48
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,480
It's perfectly safe.
这里绝对安全。

49
00:02:32,480 --> 00:03:01,480
There isn't anyone.
没人在。

50
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:07,040
I don't think things are turning out very well for our housewives and Armand.
我觉得我们的主妇们和阿曼德的情况不太妙。

51
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:12,960
Apparently, the police officer is not going to make it to the next episode.
显然，那位警察是赶不上下一集了。

52
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:13,960
Uh-oh.
哎呀。

53
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,960
All right.
好了。

54
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:19,200
So, we saw some really great vocabulary and even though it's kind of a scary story, there
我们学到了一些很棒的词汇，虽然这是个有点吓人的故事，但

55
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,720
is a lot of things we can learn.
有很多东西可以学。

56
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:25,360
So why don't we take a look at it now in Language Takeaway.
那我们不如现在就在“语言精华”环节来看看吧。

57
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,360
Language Takeaway.
语言精华。

58
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:34,120
Well, we're going to look at five words and phrases here and the first one, they described
我们要看五个单词和短语，第一个，他们把这个女人描述成一种

59
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,720
this woman as a kind of creature.
生物。

60
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:37,720
Creature.
生物。

61
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,720
Creature.
生物。

62
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:39,720
All right.
好的。

63
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,360
So, what exactly is a creature?
那么，生物到底是什么？

64
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,680
Well, a creature can be any animal.
嗯，生物可以是任何动物。

65
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,680
Any animal?
任何动物？

66
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:48,560
Yeah, like from a mouse to a bird to an insect or a bug.
对，比如从老鼠到鸟，再到昆虫或小虫子。

67
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,840
So I can say a bird is a flying creature.
所以可以说鸟是一种会飞的生物。

68
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:51,840
Exactly.
没错。

69
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,840
All right.
好的。

70
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:57,360
You can also use it to mean an unknown and scary animal.
你也可以用它来表示一种未知且吓人的动物。

71
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:59,840
So there's a creature under my bed.
所以我床底下有个生物。

72
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,840
Yes.
是的。

73
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,960
Or some type of creature was attacking me.
或者某种生物在攻击我。

74
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:04,960
Okay.
好的。

75
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:09,080
So, a creature can be any sort of living thing or animal.
所以，生物可以是任何有生命的东西或动物。

76
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,080
Exactly.
没错。

77
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,080
Yep.
嗯。

78
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,080
All right.
好的。

79
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,080
What about our next one?
下一个词呢？

80
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,080
Well, the creature broke free from some ropes.
嗯，那个生物挣脱了绳子。

81
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,080
All right.
好的。

82
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,560
So, to break free.
那么，关于“挣脱”。

83
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,560
Break free.
挣脱。

84
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,560
Uh-huh.
嗯哼。

85
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,560
And what does that mean?
那是什么意思？

86
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:23,640
When you break free, you escape from something that stops you moving.
当你挣脱时，你从阻碍你行动的东西中逃脱出来。

87
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,640
Okay.
好的。

88
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:27,160
So, you have the ability to move again.
所以，你又能行动了。

89
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,160
Yes.
是的。

90
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,560
You break free from maybe ropes.
你可能是从绳索中挣脱出来。

91
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,920
Or chains.
或者锁链。

92
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,280
Or even a relationship.
甚至是一段关系。

93
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,280
Okay.
好的。

94
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:36,880
So, I can say, oh, I finally broke free from that awful relationship.
所以，我可以说，哦，我终于摆脱了那段糟糕的关系。

95
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,880
Mm-hmm.
嗯哼。

96
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,520
Now, that's quite interesting the way we can use this in different ways.
现在，我们能用它表达不同意思，这挺有趣的。

97
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:44,680
So why don't we take a look at some examples now?
那我们不如现在来看一些例子吧？

98
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:48,200
Example one.
例子一。

99
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:55,000
Somebody tied up the dog, but he is trying to break free.
有人把狗拴住了，但它正试图挣脱。

100
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:59,160
Example two.
例子二。

101
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:05,360
I'm glad that I broke free from that horrible relationship.
我很高兴摆脱了那段可怕的关系。

102
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:09,800
Example three.
例子三。

103
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:14,520
I want to break free from all my daily responsibilities.
我想摆脱所有日常责任。

104
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:17,120
Okay.
好的。

105
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,680
So break free, it's clear now.
所以“挣脱”，现在清楚了。

106
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,680
Mm-hmm.
嗯哼。

107
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,040
So why don't we move on to our next word?
那我们不如继续看下一个词？

108
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:24,800
They thought that maybe this creature was a kidnapper.
他们以为这个生物可能是个绑架犯。

109
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,800
Kidnapper.
绑架犯。

110
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,800
Kidnapper.
绑架犯。

111
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,800
Okay.
好的。

112
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,800
So this is?
所以这是？

113
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,800
A criminal.
一个罪犯。

114
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,800
So, a kidnapper is a criminal.
所以，绑架犯是罪犯。

115
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,800
Yep.
是的。

116
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,800
All right.
好的。

117
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,720
And what exactly does a kidnapper do?
那绑架犯具体做什么？

118
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:39,960
A kidnapper takes someone to a place and keeps them there against their will.
绑架犯把某人带到某个地方，并违背其意愿关押在那里。

119
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:40,960
Against their will.
违背其意愿。

120
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:41,960
With force or violence.
使用武力或暴力。

121
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:42,960
All right.
好吧。

122
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,200
So, I guess that makes sense, right?
所以，我想这说得通，对吧？

123
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,920
Because the word has kid in it.
因为这个词里有“kid”（孩子）。

124
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,920
Yeah.
是的。

125
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,920
So, it can take children.
所以，它可以指绑架儿童。

126
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,920
Yes.
对。

127
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,600
But it can be also, you can kidnap an adult.
但也可以，你可以绑架一个成年人。

128
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,600
Yes, that's true.
是的，没错。

129
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,600
All right.
好吧。

130
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,120
So, this word can actually be used in three different ways.
所以，这个词实际上可以有三种不同的用法。

131
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,160
So we saw a kidnapper, right?
我们看到了“kidnapper”（绑架者），对吧？

132
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,520
Okay, that is the person.
好的，那是指人。

133
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,520
Yeah.
是的。

134
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,240
And the verb, to kidnap.
还有动词，“to kidnap”（绑架）。

135
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,400
Okay.
好的。

136
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,160
Or a noun describing an action, a kidnapping.
或者一个描述动作的名词，“a kidnapping”（绑架事件）。

137
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,160
A kidnapping.
绑架事件。

138
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,160
Very good.
非常好。

139
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:09,040
Yeah, a kidnapping took place today.
是的，今天发生了一起绑架事件。

140
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,040
Okay.
好的。

141
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:11,520
So, very interesting word.
所以，这是一个非常有趣的词。

142
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:14,320
And of course, it's illegal to be a kidnapper.
当然，当绑架者是违法的。

143
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:15,320
Yes.
是的。

144
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:18,400
But this word is also very serious and it's also a crime, right?
但这个词也很严肃，而且也是一种犯罪，对吧？

145
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,400
That's right.
没错。

146
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,400
A rapist.
强奸犯。

147
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,400
A rapist.
强奸犯。

148
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,400
A rapist.
强奸犯。

149
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,400
Okay.
好的。

150
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,400
So, that is a person that...
所以，那是指一个人...

151
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,680
Who forces someone to have sex.
强迫别人发生性关系的人。

152
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,680
Okay.
好的。

153
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,960
So, again, against their will.
所以，再次强调，是违背他们的意愿。

154
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:29,960
Right.
对。

155
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:30,960
Like a kidnapper.
就像绑架者一样。

156
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:31,960
Exactly.
完全正确。

157
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:32,960
Okay.
好的。

158
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:33,960
And the verb would be...
而动词会是...

159
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,960
To rape.
强奸。

160
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:35,960
To rape.
强奸。

161
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:36,960
To rape someone.
强奸某人。

162
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:37,960
Okay.
好的。

163
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:40,440
So, on the lighter side, we heard the police officer say something in a very strange way.
所以，轻松一点来说，我们听到警察用一种很奇怪的方式说了句话。

164
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,840
He said, let me see your eyes, please.
他说，请让我看看你的眼睛。

165
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:43,840
Okay.
好的。

166
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:46,640
And this is an interesting phrase.
这是一个有趣的短语。

167
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:50,000
It's a sound made from pushing two words together.
这是由两个单词连读发出的声音。

168
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Right.
对。

169
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
So, let me.
所以，“let me”。

170
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:57,880
Why don't we hear a few more examples of this and see if we can figure out what are the
我们不如再听几个例子，看看能不能弄清楚是哪两个单词。

171
00:06:57,880 --> 00:07:01,320
two words.
两个单词。

172
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:04,040
Example one.
例子一。

173
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:08,520
Let me have a look inside the car.
让我看看车里。

174
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:11,760
Example two.
例子二。

175
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,600
Let me go out tonight, dad.
爸爸，今晚让我出去吧。

176
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,720
Example three.
例子三。

177
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:24,760
Let me think about it and I'll give you an answer tomorrow.
让我想想，明天给你答复。

178
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:29,520
So, basically, let me is...
所以，基本上，“let me”就是……

179
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,520
Let me.
“Let me”。

180
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,520
Let me.
“Let me”。

181
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,520
Yeah.
是的。

182
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,720
Let me have that pen.
把那支笔给我。

183
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,720
Okay.
好的。

184
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,720
Let me see.
让我看看。

185
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:38,600
Now, we do this also with other words, right?
我们也会用其他单词这样连读，对吧？

186
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,600
Yeah.
是的。

187
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,240
Another example would be give me.
另一个例子是“give me”。

188
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,240
Give me.
“Give me”。

189
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,240
Yeah.
是的。

190
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,240
Give me.
“Give me”。

191
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,240
Exactly.
没错。

192
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,240
Okay.
好的。

193
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,240
So, an interesting thing.
所以，有趣的是。

194
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,240
It's not proper English, right?
这不是标准的英语，对吧？

195
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,240
No.
不是。

196
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,240
You wouldn't really write it this way.
你不会真的这样写。

197
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,840
Or find it in the dictionary.
